Sentencas: Doped ceria-carbonate electrolytes have high ionic conductivity and shows good solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) performance at low temperature (400-600 A degrees C).
Titulo: Analysis of gadolinium-doped ceria-ternary carbonate composite electrolytes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Various compositions of unary, binary, and ternary gadolinium-doped ceria-carbonate electrolytes are prepared using (Na, Li, K, Sr)-CO3 and GDC.
Titulo: Analysis of gadolinium-doped ceria-ternary carbonate composite electrolytes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrolytes are physically and electrochemically characterized using X-ray diffraction, scanning electron microscopy, energy dispersive spectroscopy, and two-probe AC-conductivity methods.
Titulo: Analysis of gadolinium-doped ceria-ternary carbonate composite electrolytes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In the unary gadolinium-doped ceria-carbonate composite electrolytes, best ionic conductivity is shown by 25 wt% Li2CO3-GDC electrolyte (0.077 S cm(-1) at 600 A degrees C).
Titulo: Analysis of gadolinium-doped ceria-ternary carbonate composite electrolytes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The ternary carbonate composite mixture of 25 wt% (LiNaK)(2)CO3-GDC exhibits higher ionic conductivity (0.29 S cm(-1) at 600 A degrees C) than binary and unary carbonate electrolytes.
Titulo: Analysis of gadolinium-doped ceria-ternary carbonate composite electrolytes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The enhanced conductivity may be due to lower eutectic temperature of (LiNaK)(2)CO3 rendering larger (LiNaK)(2)CO3-GDC interface.
Titulo: Analysis of gadolinium-doped ceria-ternary carbonate composite electrolytes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At 600 A degrees C, the peak power density for the cell of ternary carbonate, 25 wt% (LiNaK)(2)CO3-GDC electrolyte and binary carbonate, 25 wt% (LiNa)(2)CO3-GDC electrolyte is 224 mW cm(-2) (at 555 mA cm(-1)) and 180 mW cm(-2) (at 417 mA cm(-1)), which would enable them to be used as electrolytes for low-temperature SOFC.
Titulo: Analysis of gadolinium-doped ceria-ternary carbonate composite electrolytes for solid oxide fuel cells
